---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const updated = "May 13, 2026";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service · Subbun" description="The agreement between you and Subbun.">
  <article class="container-tight py-16 prose-doc">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of Subbun — the Subbun Chrome extension and
      this website (collectively, "the Service"). By installing or using the
      Service, you agree to these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>The Service</h2>
    <p>
      Subbun is a Chrome extension that translates Japanese video subtitles
      into English using Chrome's built-in on-device AI APIs. The free tier
      covers YouTube; the Pro tier unlocks the additional supported sites
      and features described on the pricing page.
    </p>

    <h2>Subscription, payment, and refunds</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Payment is handled by Lemon Squeezy, our merchant of record. Lemon
        Squeezy collects sales tax and VAT where applicable, issues invoices,
        and processes refunds.
      </li>
      <li>
        Monthly and annual subscriptions auto-renew at the price disclosed at
        purchase, until you cancel. Cancellation takes effect at the end of
        the current billing period; we don't pro-rate partial periods.
      </li>
      <li>
        Lifetime purchases are non-recurring. You receive all Pro features
        for as long as the Service exists.
      </li>
      <li>
        We offer a no-questions <strong>60-day refund</strong> on Pro
        purchases, processed by Lemon Squeezy. Request via
        <a href="mailto:support@subbun.com">support@subbun.com</a> with your
        order number.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>License</h2>
